    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Moves the currentNodeto the firstvisiblechild of the current node, and returns the found child. It also moves the current node to this child. If no such child exists, returnsnulland the current node is not changed. Note that the node returned byfirstChild()is dependent on the value ofwhatToShowset during instantiation of theTreeWalkerobject. Assuming the following HTML tree, and if you set thewhatToShowtoNodeFilter.SHOW_ALLa call tofirstChild()will return aTextnode and not anHTMLDivElementobject"
